# API Route Rules

## Conventions

- All API routes must export `const dynamic = "force-dynamic"` — the manifest and framework data change at runtime.
- Return `NextResponse.json(...)` for JSON endpoints.
- Use `loadConfig()` from `@/lib/config` for reading hub config. It has its own cache with invalidation on file change.
- Use `getManifest()` from `@/lib/manifest-store` for the scanned artifact manifest.
- Use `loadFrameworkCatalog()` from `@/lib/framework` for PM AI Partner Framework data. It caches with 60s TTL.

## Existing Endpoints

| Route | Purpose |
|---|---|
| `/api/manifest` | Returns full scanned manifest JSON |
| `/api/regenerate` | POST — triggers workspace rescan |
| `/api/file/[...path]` | Serves workspace files; markdown rendered as styled HTML |
| `/api/framework` | Returns parsed framework catalog (skills, MCPs, commands, health) |
| `/api/resolve` | Resolves artifact relative path to absolute filesystem path |

## Security

- The file-serving route (`/api/file/`) only serves files within configured workspaces. Never allow path traversal outside workspace roots.
- Never expose `hub.config.ts` contents via API — it contains personal paths.
